  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Part Time Programme Assistant",
  "description": "<p>1. Ensure smooth running of daily operations of the programmes in CampusImpact, which includes planning and conducting programmes that will develop the students’ social and emotional competencies.</p>\n<p>2. To interact with the students on a regular basis over a prolonged duration through positive mentoring support for students.</p>\n<p>3. To connect with students, build positive relationships and contribute to the holistic development of the students.</p>\n<p>4. To observe, identify and listen out for some of the key needs of the students.</p>\n<p>5. To provide para-counselling support for students who have been identified with potential issues. If deemed necessary, the students will be referred for appropriate interventions.</p>\n<p>6. To plan and conduct programmes customised to students' needs and integrated to CampusImpact's efforts in character developmenet in consultation with the Programme Executive and leadership team at CampusImpact.</p>\n<p>7. To manage or liaise with stakeholders, which includes beneficiaries, volunteers and parents.</p>\n<p>8. To act in all respects according to the reasonable instructions and directions given to you by the leadership team at CampusImpact.</p>\n<p>9. You shall abide to all legal and appropriate directions, rules and practices set out in the constitution of CampusImpact and the laws of the Republic of Singapore.</p>",
